Exercise 10.7. Is an ActionListener a command object in the sense of the COMMAND
pattern?
An ActionListener is not a command object like in the Command pattern. You cannot change the state of a
concrete ActionListener and it might not have a state. The ActionListener is also not made for creating
collections of commands.

Exercise 10.9. Is the BorderFactory class of the Java library an example of the FACTORY
METHOD pattern?
The BorderFactory class is not an example of the Factory Method pattern. It does not have creator subclasses
that provide different versions of the factory method.

Exercise 9.19. Modify the algorithm animation program so that it becomes a framework
for animating different sorting algorithms. Demonstrate the framework by animating
the selection sort algorithm.